After more hopeful prospects in spring and summer, families are again more pessimistic about the change in their financial situation.
For the coming year, the majority of the population expects the situation to worsen further, with only one in ten expecting an improvement.
A Gallup poll conducted in December found that 71% of respondents - a historic high - rated the prime minister's work as "more bad than good".
Thirteen percent of those surveyed have great confidence or confidence in Ferenc Gyurcsány in general, while the share of supporters for Viktor Orbán is 38 percent.
